{
  "texts": [
    "SST-2 (Socher et al., 2013) and TweetEval (Barbieri et al., 2020) are considered as additional datasets for sentiment classification, which were not presented in the main text.",
    "SST-2 (Stanford Sentiment Treebank) corpus consists of movie reviews provided by Pang and Lee (2005) which are classified as either positive or negative.",
    "TweetEval consists of seven heterogeneous tasks based on tweets from Twitter.",
    "Here, the focus is on the tweetemotion task where each tweet is classified as joy, sadness, optimism or anger.",
    "These two datasets are included here as they have shorter inputs texts than IMDb, Yelp and Amazon."
  ]
}